02/04/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Technical committees from Kosovo and Macedonia met in Pristina on Tuesday (April 1st) to launch negotiations aimed at resolving border demarcation issues.
The first meeting was held behind closed doors under the mediation of the International Civilian Office in Kosovo.
The dispute covers an area of 2,500 hectares.
Under a deal signed between Belgrade and Skopje in 2001, the land belongs to Macedonia.
(Koha Ditore, Zeri - 02/04/08;
RTK, KTV, Makfax - 01/04/08)
